<br>
After reading a few of the other threads regarding this on this board, I came away with the feeling that there existed two major camps on the subject:<br>
<br>
1) Root would over power us, since it adds functionality to mages that would step on the toes of other classes, and would give those mages that can charm solo too much soloing power.<br>
<br>
2) Root would not over power us, since just about every other casting class gets a form of root/snare, along with other abilities that are useful from a purely defensive standpoint (Evac, FD, etc).<br>
<br>
I've viewed some of the suggestions on these boards as to how a root could be given to mages w/o making us overpowered (one such suggestion was giving mages a lvl 64 spell that had the same qualities of the lvl 4 wizzard root).<br>
<br>
After thinking about it for a good 10 minutes (yes, 10 WHOLE minutes) I can only come up with one idea that would satisfy me...<br>
<br>
<br>
Create a lvl 61 mage AA that costs about 10 points.<br>
<br>
This ability, when used casts an 1 second cast time Root with maybe 10/15 second max duration, that is easily broken from damage dealt to the mob.  This root should not be UNresistable of course, but not easily resisted either.  Then give the AA a 60 minute reuse delay.  To top things off, code the spell in such a way that it CANNOT be overwritten by any actual root/snare, mez (neither normal nor summoned only), or charm ( neither normal nor summoned only).<br>
<br>
This is what I like to think of as the &quot;Hooray, Time to Gate&quot; AA.<br>
<br>
The relatively short duration of the root allows little time to do anything aside from either gating, running like hell, or summoning a pet (no time to buff it, sorry).  The 60 minute reuse delay obviously reduces the amount a mage can use the ability, limiting its use in group or solo situations.  While the &quot;No Overwritting&quot; thing isn't a HUGE problem for the soloing mage (since he could simpy wait for the root to break, THEN mez/charm the charging Summoned being) it is obviously not TOO overpowering (since a soloing mage would STILL have the once-charmed mob stampeding at him).  And of course the fact that a relatively small amount of damage would break the root reduces the usefulness of this root from a &quot;that mob is KILLING my pet, I better root it and gate, while my pet keeps on beating on it&quot; to a &quot;that mob just KILLED my pet and is beating the crap out of me, I better root it and gate&quot; spell.<br>
<br>
That's the way I personally envision such an ability for mages.  Not too overpowering, but a nice &quot;Get Out of Death Free&quot; card for when a green mob is gonna kill ya.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vmtankersley/eyeofknobbysig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
